The paper deals with signal processing on graphs, which is a topic that can be categorized under several sub-fields of computer science. The use of transforms and dictionaries to identify and exploit structure in signals on weighted graphs suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Signal Processing (cs.SI), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents a fast algorithm for the proposed transform, which could indicate that it belongs to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the potential applications of the proposed transform include image processing, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
